article_title: Europe urges unity on Taliban but is quiet on failed mission
meta_description: LONDON (AP) — Like much of the world, European countries have looked on with dismay as two decades of a U.S-led Western campaign in Afghanistan collapsed within hours.  Britain and other European nations say they will not recognize any government formed by the Taliban and want the West to work together on a common stance.
